## Testing plan

Gates that apply to this slice (all run by the supervisor): `build`, `unit-tests`, `constructor-unit-tests`.

- `build` (`Berreman/`): `dotnet build Berreman.slnx -c Release` MUST succeed with the five new projects (plus the test project) present and the UI project building WITHOUT the FuncUI clone dependency.
- `unit-tests` (`Berreman/BerremanTests/`): existing `BerremanTests` suite MUST stay green (count_at_least baseline 0 for the first slice of the arc).
- `constructor-unit-tests`: `dotnet test ‚Ä¶ OpticalConstructor.Tests.fsproj -c Release` MUST run and pass. Add the Part A solution-layout test asserting the five projects exist with `x64` platform and build/compile in one pass with no new C# project, and that the engine is referenced, not copied (AC-A1; engine-reuse directives A.2/A.3). Add beam-tree construction tests for the mirror special case (a non-mirror node exposes two outgoing beams; a `Transmitted` attach to a mirror node is rejected; a `Reflected` attach is accepted) (AC-A3, AC-A4). Add a JSON round-trip / schema-validation smoke test over the skeleton aggregate (AC-A2).
- Emit the mandatory state-of-the-world file with the `gates:` YAML baseline block (see Hand-off).

## Risks

- **Medium:** `Berreman.slnx` edit + five new `.fsproj` targeting .NET 10 with `x64` platform must build cleanly; mis-ordered project references or a stray UI‚Üíclone reference will fail the `build` gate. Keep the UI/App projects as minimal buildable skeletons authored against the FuncUI DSL surface as source, with NO clone dependency (R-6/R-9, ¬ß0 constraint 5).
- **Medium:** the root aggregate has forward references to types introduced by later slices (B beam tree detail, D materials/units, E sources, H chart settings). Keep the slice-001 aggregate minimal so it compiles; later slices extend it. The reflection-based FSharp.SystemTextJson converter serializes added fields automatically, so the serialization seam keeps compiling as the aggregate grows.

## Hand-off

State carried to later slices:
- The five projects exist under `Berreman/OpticalConstructor/`, build green, and are wired in `Berreman.slnx` with `x64`. `OpticalConstructor.Tests` exists and is the `constructor-unit-tests` target ‚Äî every later slice adds its tests here.
- `BeamBranch`, `ConstructorElement`, `BeamNode`, `BeamTree`, `BeamNode.attach`, and `BeamTreeError` live in `Domain/BeamTree.fs`. Slice 003 (Part B) adds the per-node solver-driving, propagation routing, and the default-unit hook; slice 004 (Part C) extends the tree with curved elements.
- `OpticalConstructorProject` (skeleton) lives in `Domain/OpticalConstructorProject.fs`. Slice 002 adds materials + per-element `defaultUnit`; slice 005 adds `sources`; slice 008 adds `chartSettings`. The reflection-based serializer in `Storage/ProjectJson.fs` extends automatically.
- The schema scaffold `optical-constructor-project.schema.json` carries the nine `$def` anchors; Parts B‚ÄìG fill the physics-shaped `$defs`; slice 009 (Part I) wires validate-on-load.
- The units-spine architecture (R-10) is fixed; slice 002 authors `Domain/Units.fs` (`UnitOfMeasure` + conversions).

Per `arc-runner.system-md`, the worker MUST emit the state-of-the-world file with a fenced YAML `gates:` block carrying this round's baseline counts, e.g.:

```yaml
gates:
  berreman_unit_tests: <int>
```

The `berreman_unit_tests` baseline is the `Passed:` count captured by the `unit-tests` gate this round; later slices' `count_at_least` gate reads it from this block.
